commits.message:
No ticket: Run i18n-health on PR pushes on branch, not main (#924)

When we run our i18n-tasks health GitHub Action on push to a PR, it used to run on main instead of the code in the PR. Now, it will run on the code in the PR.
commits.author: Tim Miller

commits.message:
remove now unused strings (#923)

1. A ticket copied an error banner to /summary but did not copy two strings that it required. These strings have now been copied.
2. There were three strings that were no longer used at all. These have been deleted.
commits.author: Tim Miller

commits.message:
FFS-3214: add w2 monthly summary to pdfs (#910)

* Adds the W2 Monthly Summary component to the pdfs
* Minor changes to the Payments and Deductions list
* Per convo with Rutvi, only show the footnote for the first of each type of employment
commits.author: Tim Miller

commits.message:
Filter `member_name` and `employer_name` from logs (#921)

The filter parameters are applied recursively to anything in the
`params` hash so they don't get logged.

Let's make sure that these fields from within the
`cbv_flow_invitations.income_changes` object are redacted before being
logged to NewRelic.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Remove Pat from reviewer lottery (#922)

His last day at DSAC was Friday. So long!
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message: Upgrade webpack from 5.99.9 to 5.101.0 (#919)
commits.author: decause-gov

commits.message:
FFS-3203: adding w2 monthly summary to /summary page (#906)

* The /summary page will now display the same W2 Monthly Summary view component that we display on /payment_details. The footnote will always be hidden per a conversation with Rutvi.
* This page's headers are now correct (previously we'd skip a level here and there). Note that these might look a little funny right now, but will look normal again once Tom's big css change PRs are in.
commits.author: Tim Miller

commits.message:
Increase RDS ACU capacity to 10 (#915)

This is part of our tried-and-true load tested configuration, we need to
set this in order to achieve the necessary performance.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Improve styling of process list (#901)

* Use the `usa-process-list__heading` class for the headings
* Remove the unnecessary spacing helper classes
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Improve display of "Copy Link" on /success (#904) * Add slightly more margin between icons and the text for each step * Use `

` tags more consistently and rely on their spacing instead of using helper classes * Move the "Copy Link" button into the `usa-icon-list` so it doesn't need to reinvent its left margin
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Add spacing below alerts in layout (#903)

This will improve the distinctiveness of these alerts by separating them
from the content properly.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Ensure consistent margin on "Continue" buttons (#900)

* Remove custom styling for `.usa-button.display-block` as it diverges
  from intended button styling in Figma
* Override button spacing to be 5 units to match Figma (instead of the
  default of 3) when inside a .usa-form.
* Update help modal buttons (and cleanup other styling)
* Create `help-modal__button` CSS class to handle its rules. It adds a
  bit more line height than standard.
* Make "Continue" buttons have equal top/bottom margin
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
FFS-2839: Remove "usa-prose" class by configuring USWDS (#902)

We don't need the usa-prose class after enabling
`$theme-global-content-styles`, which will create CSS rules for common
HTML elements according to USWDS typography. This creates some styles
that are not consistent with our Figma template, though: namely the
heading font and font sizes.

This also updates some other global styles, such as the measure and
changing our body font to be "Public Sans" instead of "Source Sans Pro"
to match Figma.
commits.author: Tom Dooner

commits.message:
Skip tracking ApplicantClickedGenericLink for Go user agent (#916)

We're still not exactly sure what this traffic is from, but we tend to
get about 80k requests from a Go-Http-Client user agent when the LA SMS
messages go out.

These events clutter up the Mixpanel account and delay other async jobs
from succeeding.

Until we figure out a more effective rate limiting strategy, let's at
least stop tracking these useless bot events.
commits.author: Tom Dooner
